1
00:00:00,093 --> 00:00:01,905
Previously on "Ugly Betty"...

2
00:00:01,915 --> 00:00:04,593
Why do they say that's not
your social security number?

3
00:00:04,603 --> 00:00:07,338
You can't get one if you're
in this country illegally.

4
00:00:07,348 --> 00:00:08,631
I need you to find my watch.

5
00:00:08,641 --> 00:00:11,203
Pretty sure I left it at some
woman's apartment last week.

6
00:00:11,213 --> 00:00:13,356
He dates anything that moves,

7
00:00:13,366 --> 00:00:16,142
and I agree to smile
and take their messages.

8
00:00:16,152 --> 00:00:20,148
You may want to return some of these.
Nico's called twice.

9
00:00:20,158 --> 00:00:21,564
Hi, mom.

10
00:00:21,577 --> 00:00:24,260
Who's filling his head with
stories about me and Fey?

11
00:00:24,273 --> 00:00:25,665
Who gave my son the music box?

12
00:00:25,678 --> 00:00:30,529
I think it's time for Fey
Sommers to come out of seclusion.

13
00:00:32,339 --> 00:00:34,721
He could be deported?

14
00:00:36,279 --> 00:00:38,372
Very strong possibility, yes.

15
00:00:38,387 --> 00:00:40,132
But he has a family.

16
00:00:40,146 --> 00:00:42,653
He pays taxes. He's a Mets fan.

17
00:00:42,665 --> 00:00:43,962
He's in Oprah's book club.

18
00:00:43,977 --> 00:00:47,400
Given what you've told me, it's likely
your father's been red-flagged.

19
00:00:47,418 --> 00:00:50,100
Red-flagged? Is that bad?

20
00:00:50,117 --> 00:00:52,963
It means that the government is
investigating, and ultimately,

21
00:00:52,975 --> 00:00:55,752
a judge could rule to have
you sent back to Mexico.

22
00:00:55,765 --> 00:00:57,620
You coulda just said "bad."

23
00:00:57,637 --> 00:00:59,531
Mr. Suarez,
there's something I have to ask.

24
00:00:59,546 --> 00:01:01,900
You've been here for what,
30 years?

25
00:01:01,916 --> 00:01:04,142
All that time,
you never applied for a green card.

26
00:01:04,157 --> 00:01:06,683
Never began the
citizenship process.

27
00:01:06,697 --> 00:01:08,600
What about the
amnesty in the '80s?

28
00:01:08,616 --> 00:01:10,803
I was a little busy
providing for my family.

29
00:01:10,815 --> 00:01:11,900
Is that such a problem?

30
00:01:11,917 --> 00:01:12,912
Dad.

31
00:01:12,926 --> 00:01:15,052
Look, the past is past.

32
00:01:15,065 --> 00:01:17,033
I wanna talk about now.

33
00:01:17,048 --> 00:01:19,500
How much will it cost
for you to help us?

34
00:01:19,515 --> 00:01:20,962
Now this meeting was pro bono.

35
00:01:20,975 --> 00:01:24,602
My wife asked me because she
loves your daughter's products.

36
00:01:24,617 --> 00:01:28,412
Hilda, by the way,
that fiber loss really cleaned her out.

37
00:01:28,428 --> 00:01:30,850
But a case like this...

38
00:01:30,868 --> 00:01:32,982
you wanna save your father...

39
00:01:33,267 --> 00:01:35,401
it starts with a retainer.

40
00:01:38,715 --> 00:01:41,130
20 grand?

41
00:01:41,447 --> 00:01:43,633
Do you validate?

42
00:01:44,975 --> 00:01:46,601
Hey, slow down.

43
00:01:46,616 --> 00:01:48,910
Oh, after last night,
I think I need a walker.

44
00:01:48,926 --> 00:01:49,841
We are late.

45
00:01:49,856 --> 00:01:52,523
Wilhelmina's meeting about the
"Must Mode" issue's about to start.

46
00:01:52,538 --> 00:01:54,413
Cruella devil can wait.

47
00:01:54,425 --> 00:01:56,860
Hey, your lost watch--
did you ever figure out

48
00:01:56,875 --> 00:01:59,970
- which girl's apartment you left it at?
- No, Betty never told me.

49
00:02:07,127 --> 00:02:09,210
We should probably take
separate elevators.

50
00:02:09,225 --> 00:02:11,520
Wouldn't want the office
getting the wrong idea.

51
00:02:11,537 --> 00:02:13,640
Right. Because my panties
stuffed in your paper shredder

52
00:02:13,676 --> 00:02:16,071
probably didn't tip 'em off.

53
00:02:35,238 --> 00:02:36,923
Great.

54
00:02:36,938 --> 00:02:38,450
Just great.

55
00:02:38,468 --> 00:02:41,602
Could I help you out? I got a lot
of women's clothes up in my office.

56
00:02:41,615 --> 00:02:42,440
Hold this, please.

57
00:02:42,458 --> 00:02:44,630
Fashionable clothes...
up in the office.

58
00:02:44,646 --> 00:02:46,580
What are you doing?

59
00:02:46,597 --> 00:02:49,261
You gotta do what you gotta do.

60
00:02:49,566 --> 00:02:52,871
Fastest first date
I've ever had.

61
00:02:52,885 --> 00:02:55,112
You can't be serious.

62
00:02:55,427 --> 00:02:59,852
You actually think you've
got a shot here, now?

63
00:02:59,866 --> 00:03:01,691
Just joking.

64
00:03:02,006 --> 00:03:04,061
You smiled at me in the lobby.

65
00:03:04,078 --> 00:03:06,942
I smiled 'cause I couldn't believe
you pulled a ditch and dash

66
00:03:06,955 --> 00:03:09,162
with that poor girl back there.

67
00:03:11,708 --> 00:03:14,332
You let it all play out in your head,
didn't you?

68
00:03:14,348 --> 00:03:16,001
You, me,

69
00:03:16,018 --> 00:03:18,151
no one else here.

70
00:03:18,167 --> 00:03:22,042
We'd be on the floor,
bodies sweating,

71
00:03:22,058 --> 00:03:24,823
rug burn on my back.

72
00:03:26,396 --> 00:03:31,072
Well, so much for that fantasy.

73
00:03:33,615 --> 00:03:36,563
As we do every year for
our "Must Mode" issue,

74
00:03:36,578 --> 00:03:41,562
your ideas, your picks, your lists
will be considered for inclusion.

75
00:03:49,505 --> 00:03:52,601
Nico,  I told you,
only emergencies.

76
00:03:52,698 --> 00:03:56,581
No, you cannot submit my
apartment for "Pimp Yo House."

77
00:03:56,595 --> 00:03:58,201
Good-bye.

78
00:03:59,755 --> 00:04:03,223
Family is staying
with me temporarily.

79
00:04:03,237 --> 00:04:05,160
Remember, it's not
just an "it" list.

80
00:04:05,176 --> 00:04:07,883
There are personal
"musts" as well.

81
00:04:07,895 --> 00:04:11,600
Like must be on time.

82
00:04:11,898 --> 00:04:15,160
For others,
it's a bit more profound.

83
00:04:15,178 --> 00:04:18,100
What's important is that
we tap into the issues

84
00:04:18,115 --> 00:04:20,980
of our readers' lives
they cannot face,

85
00:04:20,997 --> 00:04:24,073
move them to the next
stage in their lives,

86
00:04:24,085 --> 00:04:26,381
promise them it
won't be another year

87
00:04:26,397 --> 00:04:31,170
full of unanswered questions
and unresolved issues,

88
00:04:31,185 --> 00:04:33,002
and lest we forget,

89
00:04:33,015 --> 00:04:37,050
it is about the fashion
"must-haves" for 2007,

90
00:04:37,065 --> 00:04:41,923
and I can assure you it will
not include polka-dots.

91
00:04:41,937 --> 00:04:43,560
That's it.

92
00:04:43,578 --> 00:04:45,561
Start listing.

93
00:04:48,815 --> 00:04:51,811
You have an 11:30 layout conference,
and your father's office called.

94
00:04:51,826 --> 00:04:53,732
There's an editors-in-chief
meeting tomorrow.

95
00:04:53,748 --> 00:04:57,003
So listen, there's this
woman--smoking hot--works on 27.

96
00:04:57,016 --> 00:04:59,012
She's not wearing a shirt,
had some sort of accident.

97
00:04:59,045 --> 00:05:02,100
I really--I need you to
find out who she is, okay?

98
00:05:02,846 --> 00:05:06,402
"Must" hunt down Daniel's babe.

99
00:05:08,136 --> 00:05:10,531
Whatever Bradford Meade does,

100
00:05:10,546 --> 00:05:12,510
he can't get rid ome.

101
00:05:12,528 --> 00:05:15,561
Sometimes it's like
she's still here.

102
00:05:17,147 --> 00:05:21,082
You remember what tomorrow is,
don't you?

103
00:05:23,095 --> 00:05:25,360
How could I forget?

104
00:05:32,106 --> 00:05:34,573
Nico, darling, I'm home.

105
00:05:35,938 --> 00:05:37,452
What is that?

106
00:05:37,466 --> 00:05:40,100
Dinner. You didn't have much.

107
00:05:40,116 --> 00:05:41,650
My wine,

108
00:05:41,667 --> 00:05:44,201
and pecorino di pienza.

109
00:05:44,395 --> 00:05:47,033
It's a cheese.
Goes great with pears.

110
00:05:47,045 --> 00:05:49,531
And cereal goes
great with milk.

111
00:05:49,546 --> 00:05:51,231
How  was your day, dear?

112
00:05:51,247 --> 00:05:53,171
I picked these up today--

113
00:05:53,185 --> 00:05:55,613
brochures for
schools in New York.

114
00:05:55,627 --> 00:05:56,880
Don't be silly.

115
00:05:56,897 --> 00:05:58,932
Schools here don't
meet your standards.

116
00:05:58,945 --> 00:06:02,311
I was thinking of the Hertzog
school in Switzerland.

117
00:06:02,326 --> 00:06:04,120
Expelled, remember?

118
00:06:04,137 --> 00:06:07,491
So I'm starting to think maybe
boarding school's not for me.

119
00:06:07,657 --> 00:06:09,572
I said the same
thing to the senator

120
00:06:09,587 --> 00:06:11,581
when he sent me to
the Chamberlin school.

121
00:06:11,596 --> 00:06:14,690
He'd just won his first
congressional seat.

122
00:06:14,706 --> 00:06:16,930
- He told me--
- "Willie, D.C. is no place

123
00:06:16,947 --> 00:06:19,313
for my daughter to
become a young lady."

124
00:06:19,327 --> 00:06:21,112
Same thing goes for
you in New York.

125
00:06:21,128 --> 00:06:23,781
Boarding school has a 
far better education,

126
00:06:23,798 --> 00:06:27,502
far better people
and far better food

127
00:06:27,518 --> 00:06:30,501
than... Captain Crisp.

128
00:06:30,517 --> 00:06:31,630
"Cap'N."

129
00:06:31,645 --> 00:06:34,810
I don't think he's an
official maritime officer.

130
00:06:37,076 --> 00:06:39,611
Dad, is this everything
from Mexico?

131
00:06:39,625 --> 00:06:42,401
Yeah, birth
certificate, passport,

132
00:06:42,418 --> 00:06:44,662
maybe even an old baby picture.

133
00:06:44,676 --> 00:06:47,022
Careful. I might be
naked in that one.

134
00:06:47,037 --> 00:06:49,620
The lawyer's gonna
need these documents.

135
00:06:49,636 --> 00:06:51,591
Yeah,  the lawyer
we can't afford.

136
00:06:51,608 --> 00:06:53,891
You know, dad, there's enough here.
You could have applied for a green card.

137
00:06:53,926 --> 00:06:57,471
I mean, you were here in '86,
and Reagan offered the amnesty.

138
00:06:57,507 --> 00:06:59,490
I, uh...

139
00:06:59,546 --> 00:07:02,080
I missed it. Okay?

140
00:07:03,508 --> 00:07:06,950
Look, I-I'm sorry I'm
putting you through all this.

141
00:07:06,967 --> 00:07:10,521
But maybe if we tighten our belts,
got second jobs, maybe--

142
00:07:10,536 --> 00:07:13,043
Dad, I really want to help, but

143
00:07:13,055 --> 00:07:15,350
my first job is hard
enough as it is.

144
00:07:15,363 --> 00:07:17,225
Not if you maximize
your time there.

145
00:07:17,238 --> 00:07:18,369
Hilda, don't go there again.

146
00:07:18,379 --> 00:07:20,201
I am not gonna sell
Herbalux at "Mode."

147
00:07:20,219 --> 00:07:23,930
What model doesn't wanna lose weight?
It's easy money.

148
00:07:24,428 --> 00:07:26,702
It's not the worst
idea in the world.

149
00:07:26,715 --> 00:07:30,451
I will set you up with a basic
package just to tease 'em.

150
00:07:31,317 --> 00:07:33,193
What's this?

151
00:07:37,227 --> 00:07:39,853
Looks like somebody
was torn out.

152
00:07:42,766 --> 00:07:45,241
Ah, it's nothing.

153
00:07:45,306 --> 00:07:49,043
Just a photo of mom
with an old boyfriend.

154
00:07:49,057 --> 00:07:50,700
Ooh, let me see.

155
00:07:51,167 --> 00:07:52,773
A boyfriend?

156
00:07:52,786 --> 00:07:55,181
I thought you said you were
each other's first loves.

157
00:07:55,196 --> 00:07:57,833
Can you stop with
the damn questions?

158
00:08:02,728 --> 00:08:04,442
I'm going for a walk.

159
00:08:05,096 --> 00:08:07,333
If it's okay, Betty.

160
00:08:10,177 --> 00:08:13,893
What is with you? Obviously,
he is sensitive about all of this.

161
00:08:13,906 --> 00:08:16,171
Well, there's something
he's not telling us.

162
00:08:16,187 --> 00:08:19,312
We're just trying to help him, Hilda.
We deserve to know.

163
00:08:19,457 --> 00:08:20,602
Doesn't that upset you?

164
00:08:20,617 --> 00:08:23,513
Of course it does,
but getting upset doesn't help.

165
00:08:23,527 --> 00:08:24,662
He's always been
there for us, Betty.

166
00:08:24,698 --> 00:08:27,593
We just--we gotta be
there for him now.

167
00:08:27,607 --> 00:08:31,062
Fine. I'll sell
Herbalux at "Mode."

168
00:08:31,076 --> 00:08:32,570
I mean,
I'd do anything I have to,

169
00:08:32,585 --> 00:08:35,111
but I'm not gonna just
let him off the hook,

170
00:08:35,127 --> 00:08:38,150
not until he tells
us the truth.

171
00:08:55,916 --> 00:08:58,041
Okay, give it back to me, girl.

172
00:08:58,058 --> 00:09:01,350
The vita valu pack contains all
essential vitamins from A to Z.

173
00:09:01,368 --> 00:09:03,422
You know there's no such
thing as vitamin Z?

174
00:09:03,438 --> 00:09:05,663
Hello, it's a
catchy sales pitch.

175
00:09:05,677 --> 00:09:08,181
And what is more important
than the vitamin content?

176
00:09:08,198 --> 00:09:11,290
You get it half off when purchased
with the nitro nutrient combo.

177
00:09:11,306 --> 00:09:13,820
Right. Now the customers
have to have confidence

178
00:09:13,836 --> 00:09:15,662
in you and the product,
so don't be afraid

179
00:09:15,677 --> 00:09:18,450
to really just put
yourself out there.

180
00:09:18,465 --> 00:09:20,653
Tired of sticking your
finger down your throat?

181
00:09:20,666 --> 00:09:23,252
Wanna lose weight the easy way?
Ask me how!

182
00:09:23,266 --> 00:09:25,352
Herbalux can help.

183
00:09:25,696 --> 00:09:28,151
It's a good line.
I might use it.

184
00:09:28,168 --> 00:09:30,691
Now you're ready for
your secret weapon.

185
00:09:30,708 --> 00:09:32,462
10 pounds in 10 days.

186
00:09:32,477 --> 00:09:34,073
Oh, god.
Do I really need to wear that?

187
00:09:34,086 --> 00:09:36,011
I remember when I got pinned.

188
00:09:36,026 --> 00:09:38,160
Shelly Jenkins
did me the honor.

189
00:09:38,177 --> 00:09:40,992
Did she get you a
limo and a corsage?

190
00:09:42,075 --> 00:09:44,703
Can I please go to work
and humiliate myself now?

191
00:09:44,715 --> 00:09:46,310
Yes. Yes, you may.

192
00:09:46,326 --> 00:09:51,071
Shelly always said, "hit 'em with
the appetizer prices before lunch."

193
00:09:52,496 --> 00:09:55,021
Happy Herbaluxing!

194
00:10:08,018 --> 00:10:09,793
Good morning, Marc.

195
00:10:09,806 --> 00:10:12,062
I think I have something here
that might interest you.

196
00:10:12,077 --> 00:10:14,650
Hmm. Unless it's Taye
Diggs covered in baby oil,

197
00:10:14,668 --> 00:10:15,450
I doubt it.

198
00:10:15,468 --> 00:10:17,531
I see that you're enjoying
a healthy smoothie.

199
00:10:17,547 --> 00:10:19,513
Did you know scientists today
are making great strides

200
00:10:19,546 --> 00:10:20,962
in the health
supplement market?

201
00:10:20,976 --> 00:10:23,123
And most of those scientists
are working in the Herbalux lab

202
00:10:23,157 --> 00:10:24,332
in Hoboken, New Jersey.

203
00:10:24,346 --> 00:10:28,131
- In fact, Herbalux--
- Could you please just--

204
00:10:28,526 --> 00:10:30,713
10 pounds?

205
00:10:31,048 --> 00:10:33,743
- Reach for the stars.
- Marc...

206
00:10:33,756 --> 00:10:36,003
we have some phone calls to make,
don't we?

207
00:10:36,015 --> 00:10:37,140
Yeah.

208
00:10:37,755 --> 00:10:40,890
Work those halls,
you little diet diva.

209
00:10:48,725 --> 00:10:52,460
I  don't like it when she smiles.
It's so metallic.

210
00:10:52,478 --> 00:10:53,823
What did she want?

211
00:10:53,836 --> 00:10:57,651
Looks like she's trying to earn
a few extra pesos for something.

212
00:10:57,667 --> 00:10:59,552
Interesting.

213
00:11:00,108 --> 00:11:03,043
What's the status on the
list of boarding schools?

214
00:11:03,058 --> 00:11:04,830
London and Milan passed.

215
00:11:04,846 --> 00:11:08,883
There's still one school in Paris
that hasn't heard of Nico, I think.

216
00:11:08,896 --> 00:11:11,531
C'est parfait.
Get them on the phone.

217
00:11:11,897 --> 00:11:14,391
Oh, and before I forget,

218
00:11:14,405 --> 00:11:16,293
you're meeting with
Daniel's been pushed.

219
00:11:16,306 --> 00:11:18,610
He's at a meeting in
Bradford's office--

220
00:11:18,626 --> 00:11:21,103
editors-in-chief only.

221
00:11:21,115 --> 00:11:24,202
Well, I'm sure Skippy's
holding his own.

222
00:11:31,998 --> 00:11:33,752
My pleasure.

223
00:11:41,678 --> 00:11:44,950
I like mine black, two sugars.

224
00:11:44,967 --> 00:11:47,011
You want me to get you coffee?

225
00:11:47,026 --> 00:11:48,840
I think that's why you're here.

226
00:11:48,858 --> 00:11:52,433
Oh, and what gave it away?
Was it my accent?

227
00:11:52,445 --> 00:11:54,570
Actually, the fact that
you're the only person here

228
00:11:54,585 --> 00:11:57,062
who doesn't edit a
Meade publication.

229
00:11:57,076 --> 00:11:59,500
You're an editor.

230
00:11:59,868 --> 00:12:03,782
Wow. I bet that gets
you all the girls, huh?

231
00:12:03,798 --> 00:12:07,472
Uh, usually, my magazine's
circulation count does the trick.

232
00:12:07,487 --> 00:12:10,161
Circulation count.

233
00:12:10,175 --> 00:12:13,251
Why? Is it big?

234
00:12:13,268 --> 00:12:15,732
Well, I don't like to brag,

235
00:12:15,746 --> 00:12:19,000
but I am in the top five.

236
00:12:19,017 --> 00:12:21,863
Oh, my god. Listen, I'm sorry.

237
00:12:21,877 --> 00:12:23,313
I'm new here,

238
00:12:23,328 --> 00:12:26,123
and I'm not really that
familiar with everyone yet.

239
00:12:26,137 --> 00:12:28,033
- Of course, I'm--
- Daniel Meade,

240
00:12:28,046 --> 00:12:29,751
"Mode" magazine--

241
00:12:29,767 --> 00:12:33,561
the only one in this room
who was born into his job.

242
00:12:33,576 --> 00:12:36,303
All right,
let's get started, everyone.

243
00:12:37,798 --> 00:12:39,312
I have news.

244
00:12:39,328 --> 00:12:42,033
Some might call
it exciting news.

245
00:12:42,046 --> 00:12:45,990
In january, Meade publishing
launches a new weekly...

246
00:12:46,007 --> 00:12:48,811
targeting the
empowered modern woman.

247
00:12:48,826 --> 00:12:50,272
You'll all get the press release.
The point is,

248
00:12:50,307 --> 00:12:53,180
that I wish to introduce
the best-selling author

