Act out as much as you want.

503
00:25:23,136 --> 00:25:24,563
I did.

504
00:25:24,578 --> 00:25:26,560
Seven schools...

505
00:25:26,576 --> 00:25:28,572
until it finally hit me...

506
00:25:28,586 --> 00:25:31,143
until I finally understood.

507
00:25:31,157 --> 00:25:34,020
Being away from home,
being away from the ones you love,

508
00:25:34,038 --> 00:25:38,000
makes you strong,
builds your armor.

509
00:25:38,316 --> 00:25:42,051
Because in the end,
the only person in this world

510
00:25:42,068 --> 00:25:45,750
you can depend on is yourself.

511
00:25:45,768 --> 00:25:49,481
It's the greatest lesson
the senator ever taught me.

512
00:25:50,365 --> 00:25:53,323
- Mom--
- Brush up on your french.

513
00:25:53,337 --> 00:25:56,693
You leave for school in
Paris tomorrow night.

514
00:26:03,366 --> 00:26:05,193
So...

515
00:26:05,206 --> 00:26:07,202
um...

516
00:26:07,388 --> 00:26:09,550
is everything okay?

517
00:26:09,567 --> 00:26:11,581
The flag was kind
of at half-mast.

518
00:26:11,597 --> 00:26:14,671
Would it be generic if I sent
you a necklace from Tiffany?

519
00:26:14,688 --> 00:26:17,151
Oh, no. I loved it.

520
00:26:17,167 --> 00:26:20,081
You sent it to me after
our first night together.

521
00:26:20,098 --> 00:26:21,772
Of course I did.

522
00:26:21,788 --> 00:26:24,252
And if I sent to you as a...

523
00:26:24,265 --> 00:26:27,012
sort of an apology,
that'd be okay, right?

524
00:26:27,028 --> 00:26:29,132
Well, that depends.

525
00:26:29,146 --> 00:26:32,960
Are you apologizing for
something in particular?

526
00:26:32,976 --> 00:26:34,343
Yeah.

527
00:26:34,357 --> 00:26:37,712
Making an ass out of
myself with Sofia Reyes,

528
00:26:37,726 --> 00:26:40,133
the editor of "M.Y.W."

529
00:26:40,146 --> 00:26:42,432
I sent her a necklace
as an apology gift,

530
00:26:42,445 --> 00:26:44,860
and she called me out on it.

531
00:26:45,138 --> 00:26:46,551
Oh.

532
00:26:46,565 --> 00:26:50,001
So the whole apology
thing was about her,

533
00:26:50,015 --> 00:26:51,220
not me.

534
00:26:51,235 --> 00:26:53,163
What do I have to
apologize to you about?

535
00:26:53,175 --> 00:26:55,230
Nothing...

536
00:26:56,107 --> 00:26:58,093
I guess.

537
00:26:59,015 --> 00:27:01,491
You know,
I'm not feeling too well.

538
00:27:01,506 --> 00:27:02,950
I think I'm gonna go.

539
00:27:02,967 --> 00:27:04,260
You okay?

540
00:27:04,277 --> 00:27:05,771
Yeah, I, uh...

541
00:27:05,787 --> 00:27:08,563
I think I feel one of those
24-hour flus coming on.

542
00:27:08,578 --> 00:27:11,732
I should go before
I get you sick.

543
00:27:47,425 --> 00:27:49,010
Whoops.

544
00:27:49,556 --> 00:27:51,510
That step's a tough one.

545
00:27:51,527 --> 00:27:54,163
Why are you sneaking
in through the back?

546
00:27:54,295 --> 00:27:55,742
Are you drunk?

547
00:27:55,757 --> 00:27:58,043
Yeah, a little bit.
I'm going to bed.

548
00:27:58,057 --> 00:27:59,473
No, no, no, no, come on.
Let me get you some water.

549
00:27:59,505 --> 00:28:00,502
- No, I'm fine.
- Come on.

550
00:28:00,516 --> 00:28:01,992
Dad, let me go!

551
00:28:02,006 --> 00:28:03,910
What's the matter with you?
What's going on?

552
00:28:03,927 --> 00:28:06,041
- Talk to me!
- Talk to you?

553
00:28:06,056 --> 00:28:09,211
Why don't you talk to me?
Why don't you tell me

554
00:28:09,227 --> 00:28:12,603
why mom is wearing a wedding
band in this picture?

555
00:28:14,228 --> 00:28:17,800
Or who's the guy in the
photo with her, really?

556
00:28:22,118 --> 00:28:23,710
There you go.

557
00:28:23,728 --> 00:28:26,720
I don't have to explain myself to you.
I'm your father.

558
00:28:26,736 --> 00:28:29,171
Then act like it.

559
00:28:30,088 --> 00:28:32,080
I've always looked
up to you, dad.

560
00:28:32,098 --> 00:28:35,160
Right, wrong,
I could just take your lead.

561
00:28:37,568 --> 00:28:39,680
Now I'm lost.

562
00:28:46,845 --> 00:28:49,163
A little less slamming, please.

563
00:28:50,567 --> 00:28:53,792
Here. You're gonna need this.

564
00:28:53,807 --> 00:28:55,202
Thanks.

565
00:28:55,247 --> 00:28:56,803
So...

566
00:28:57,677 --> 00:28:59,500
dad left early this morning.

567
00:28:59,518 --> 00:29:00,843
I don't really want
to talk about this.

568
00:29:00,875 --> 00:29:03,261
Well, it's a little
too late for that now.

569
00:29:03,275 --> 00:29:05,661
I heard what you
said last night.

570
00:29:05,678 --> 00:29:08,930
- So did half of Rego Park.
- I'm sorry.

571
00:29:08,946 --> 00:29:12,450
Apologizing to me isn't
gonna change what happened.

572
00:29:12,558 --> 00:29:15,782
What went on after I left
the office yesterday?

573
00:29:15,797 --> 00:29:18,212
I got punished.

574
00:29:28,936 --> 00:29:31,892
Is this real, or is this one
of those Ed McMahon things?

575
00:29:31,908 --> 00:29:33,640
It'll cash.

576
00:29:33,655 --> 00:29:35,712
20 grand.

577
00:29:35,726 --> 00:29:37,772
So cash it.
This is the answer--

578
00:29:37,786 --> 00:29:40,223
Hilda, look closer.

579
00:29:41,746 --> 00:29:44,231
Wilhelmina Slater?

580
00:29:44,936 --> 00:29:48,543
- Oh, that stuck-up--
- Exactly.

581
00:29:49,405 --> 00:29:51,652
She'll want me to
sell Daniel out

582
00:29:51,667 --> 00:29:53,923
so she can take his job.

583
00:29:56,595 --> 00:29:58,531
Her money, my soul.

584
00:29:58,547 --> 00:30:01,673
Look, I'm gonna try to figure
something else out, okay?

585
00:30:01,686 --> 00:30:04,220
See if there's another way.

586
00:30:04,956 --> 00:30:08,283
But this might be
our only option.

587
00:30:42,457 --> 00:30:45,701
Can I get the number
for Fashion TV, please?

588
00:30:57,615 --> 00:30:59,582
What the hell just happened?

589
00:30:59,825 --> 00:31:01,863
You're getting back at me,
aren't you?

590
00:31:01,876 --> 00:31:03,700
For yesterday?

591
00:31:03,796 --> 00:31:06,083
- You planned this.
- Planned this? Are you s--

592
00:31:06,096 --> 00:31:08,682
Yeah. I got a side job
with the elevator union.

593
00:31:08,697 --> 00:31:11,260
Really? I'll take
the stairs next time.

594
00:31:11,276 --> 00:31:12,762
Do you always get
the last word in?

595
00:31:12,775 --> 00:31:14,482
Only with you, baby.

596
00:31:14,497 --> 00:31:15,593
Great.

597
00:31:15,605 --> 00:31:18,050
Last time this happened was
four hours of Kevin Federline

598
00:31:18,065 --> 00:31:19,740
trying to cornrow my hair.

599
00:31:19,758 --> 00:31:22,092
No reception. What now?

600
00:31:22,105 --> 00:31:24,182
I think we're between floors.
If I could just get up there,

601
00:31:24,218 --> 00:31:26,710
I could pry the door
open on the next floor.

602
00:31:26,725 --> 00:31:29,910
Somebody's seen "Die
hard" too many times.

603
00:31:31,358 --> 00:31:36,132
Oh! God forbid you
wrinkle your jacket.

604
00:31:36,975 --> 00:31:40,232
Listen, how about
we do the obvious?

605
00:31:40,246 --> 00:31:42,262
Come on. Give me a boost.

606
00:31:42,276 --> 00:31:43,613
Are you serious?

607
00:31:43,626 --> 00:31:45,513
On your knees.

608
00:31:46,598 --> 00:31:49,161
And, Daniel, don't look up.

609
00:31:49,175 --> 00:31:50,960
Don't flatter yourself.

610
00:31:50,976 --> 00:31:57,043
Good, 'cause I'm not
wearing any underwear.

611
00:32:09,065 --> 00:32:10,750
You okay?

612
00:32:11,265 --> 00:32:12,861
Yeah.

613
00:32:13,915 --> 00:32:16,212
You looked, didn't you?

614
00:32:31,675 --> 00:32:33,361
Hilda.

615
00:32:33,455 --> 00:32:35,721
You gonna make me lose
another free towel?

616
00:32:35,736 --> 00:32:37,852
No, I really wanted
to talk to you.

617
00:32:37,866 --> 00:32:41,580
Um... have you ever done
any immigration work?

618
00:32:41,595 --> 00:32:43,030
In this neighborhood?

619
00:32:43,046 --> 00:32:45,442
And besides, once I got my degree,
my uncle Abraham

620
00:32:45,456 --> 00:32:48,251
turned his place into the
israeli underground railroad.

621
00:32:48,267 --> 00:32:50,440
You in some kind of trouble?

622
00:32:52,028 --> 00:32:53,901
If I tell you something,

623
00:32:53,915 --> 00:32:56,692
do we have that attorney-client
privilege thing?

624
00:32:56,706 --> 00:32:58,621
That only works if
I'm your lawyer.

625
00:32:58,636 --> 00:33:01,951
You know, but for now, you got
something stronger than that-- my word.

626
00:33:01,967 --> 00:33:04,760
And for that, it'll only cost
you a cup of coffee and a bialy.

627
00:33:04,777 --> 00:33:07,082
Come on.
I didn't feel like working out anyway.

628
00:33:15,745 --> 00:33:18,331
Still haven't cashed it, I see.

629
00:33:18,345 --> 00:33:21,171
Um, no,
I haven't really had a chance.

630
00:33:21,186 --> 00:33:23,280
Or haven't made the effort?

631
00:33:23,297 --> 00:33:25,350
Steel yourself, Betty.

632
00:33:25,365 --> 00:33:27,372
Think about what's
best for you.

633
00:33:27,387 --> 00:33:30,402
That's how we survive
in this business.

634
00:33:30,415 --> 00:33:33,012
Wilhelmina, you might want
to get down to the lobby,

635
00:33:33,025 --> 00:33:35,560
like, right now. It's Nico.

636
00:33:38,938 --> 00:33:42,351
You, too. I think we might
actually see a live execution.

637
00:33:42,367 --> 00:33:44,540
Open your eyes, people.

638
00:33:44,557 --> 00:33:46,420
It's time to wake up.

639
00:33:46,435 --> 00:33:51,910
The "Must Mode" issue promotes the
unwarranted slaughter of innocent animals.

640
00:33:51,926 --> 00:33:54,452
And it is the fault
of one woman--

641
00:33:54,466 --> 00:33:56,111
Wilhelmina Slater!

642
00:33:56,125 --> 00:33:58,023
Nico, please,
you're causing a scene

643
00:33:58,035 --> 00:33:59,071
Great.

644
00:33:59,085 --> 00:34:02,880
Can't wait to see how Wilhelmina
Slater will handle this one.

645
00:34:04,188 --> 00:34:07,112
So sorry I'm late.

646
00:34:07,126 --> 00:34:09,150
Thank you for coming.

647
00:34:09,166 --> 00:34:10,931
Ah, good to see you.

648
00:34:10,946 --> 00:34:13,991
Nico, step into the good light.

649
00:34:14,286 --> 00:34:17,350
Thank you so much for coming,
ladies and gentlemen.

650
00:34:17,365 --> 00:34:20,492
The "must" debate of 2007.

651
00:34:20,508 --> 00:34:23,592
Animal rights versus
fashion rights--

652
00:34:23,605 --> 00:34:25,750
just who is right?

653
00:34:35,146 --> 00:34:36,780
Well, you're gonna have to wait

654
00:34:36,796 --> 00:34:41,083
until the "Must Mode" issue is on sale,
january 2007.

655
00:34:41,098 --> 00:34:44,253
Thank you so much
for coming. Good-bye.

656
00:34:47,947 --> 00:34:49,613
You win.

657
00:34:49,628 --> 00:34:51,870
I'll go to school in France,

658
00:34:51,885 --> 00:34:54,952
anywhere you want,
but I'm not going quietly.

659
00:34:54,968 --> 00:34:56,723
- We'll talk upstairs.
- No!

660
00:34:56,736 --> 00:34:58,871
We'll talk now.

661
00:35:01,418 --> 00:35:04,383
- I am your mother.
- Mother?

662
00:35:04,395 --> 00:35:06,893
Then maybe you
should act like it.

663
00:35:06,907 --> 00:35:10,560
But I guess you don't have
a clue where to start.

664
00:35:10,576 --> 00:35:12,552
I mean,

665
00:35:12,718 --> 00:35:15,993
have you ever even called
the senator "dad"?

666
00:35:16,007 --> 00:35:17,421
Never, huh?

667
00:35:17,438 --> 00:35:21,533
Is that armor so thick you can't
even feel anything anymore?

668
00:35:21,597 --> 00:35:23,762
Was that the goal?

669
00:35:23,775 --> 00:35:26,160
Then congratulations.

670
00:35:26,178 --> 00:35:29,082
You're putting together
your "Must Mode" issue.

671
00:35:29,095 --> 00:35:30,852
Things you must do.

672
00:35:30,867 --> 00:35:33,292
You know what your number
one "must" should be?

673
00:35:33,306 --> 00:35:35,920
Learning how to be a mother.

674
00:35:59,345 --> 00:36:01,652
I appreciate your kindness,

675
00:36:01,665 --> 00:36:03,523
but I can't cash that.

676
00:36:03,535 --> 00:36:05,742
Of course you can't.

677
00:36:05,868 --> 00:36:09,320
Good luck with your
family situation, Betty.

678
00:36:10,045 --> 00:36:12,593
They're never easy.

679
00:36:22,136 --> 00:36:24,741
I just wanted to say good-bye.

680
00:36:24,755 --> 00:36:27,892
I think you said
enough downstairs.

681
00:36:28,246 --> 00:36:30,630
Marc booked you a
flight for Paris.

682
00:36:30,645 --> 00:36:32,281
You leave tonight at 9:00.

683
00:36:32,296 --> 00:36:34,350
I'll go back to your
place and pack my stuff.

684
00:36:34,368 --> 00:36:37,540
Nico, contrary to
what you might think,

685
00:36:37,557 --> 00:36:40,583
I do love you.

686
00:36:40,598 --> 00:36:45,111
And I...
I only want what's best for you.

687
00:36:45,125 --> 00:36:47,740
You want what's best for you.

688
00:36:58,607 --> 00:37:00,281
All right. Yeah.

689
00:37:04,476 --> 00:37:06,202
Hey.

690
00:37:08,307 --> 00:37:10,203
I had it.

691
00:37:10,726 --> 00:37:15,071
Your lost watch.
You left it at my place last week.

692
00:37:15,087 --> 00:37:17,770
Surprise. Right?

693
00:37:18,617 --> 00:37:21,940
You never even thought
to consider me.

694
00:37:21,958 --> 00:37:25,811
I'm just a late
night call to you.

695
00:37:29,915 --> 00:37:33,453
You need to find whatever it
is you're looking for, Daniel.

696
00:37:33,468 --> 00:37:37,201
I just know now
that it's not me.

697
00:37:37,216 --> 00:37:39,400
I'm--I'm sorry.

698
00:37:41,257 --> 00:37:43,243
Amanda...

699
00:37:48,537 --> 00:37:49,572
Well?

700
00:37:49,586 --> 00:37:50,943
I checked it out. Nothing.

701
00:37:50,957 --> 00:37:53,323
The security cameras at the
cemetery didn't catch a thing.

702
00:37:53,336 --> 00:37:55,640
No Fey Sommers hanging
out at her crypt.

703
00:37:55,656 --> 00:37:57,411
I saw her. I'm sure of it.

704
00:37:57,428 --> 00:38:00,982
How many times I gotta say this?
She's dead.

705
00:38:00,998 --> 00:38:02,942
You're going crazy,
you know that?

706
00:38:02,958 --> 00:38:05,723
- Damn it, I saw her.
- Whatever, old man.

707
00:38:13,366 --> 00:38:15,252
Yeah, it's me.

708
00:38:15,268 --> 00:38:18,721
Remember that associate
I told you about?

709
00:38:18,735 --> 00:38:22,150
We need to have a long
conversation about him.

710
00:39:06,518 --> 00:39:08,063
Dad.

711
00:39:09,817 --> 00:39:12,403
Do you remember when we
danced at my quinceañera,

712
00:39:12,416 --> 00:39:14,780
and I broke my heel?

713
00:39:15,056 --> 00:39:17,023
And I was so upset,
I wanted to run away,

714
00:39:17,037 --> 00:39:18,613
but you wouldn't let me.

715
00:39:18,627 --> 00:39:21,821
You just held me tighter,
and we kept on dancing.

716
00:39:23,206 --> 00:39:25,970
You're our rock, dad.

717
00:39:28,438 --> 00:39:30,653
And I'm sorry for what I said

718
00:39:30,665 --> 00:39:33,001
and how I acted.

719
00:39:33,928 --> 00:39:37,240
I'm just gonna have to
forgive and forget, and...

720
00:39:37,255 --> 00:39:40,750
whatever it is,
you don't owe us an explanation.

721
00:39:58,005 --> 00:40:00,700
Ramiro Vasquez.

722
00:40:02,345 --> 00:40:04,792
The man in the picture.

723
00:40:05,318 --> 00:40:08,472
Your mother was married to him.

724
00:40:11,217 --> 00:40:12,783
Sit.

725
00:40:18,356 --> 00:40:22,353
He was a... a wealthy man.

726
00:40:22,656 --> 00:40:24,382
I was his chef.

727
00:40:24,397 --> 00:40:27,291
Whenever I would cook
food for them, I...

728
00:40:27,956 --> 00:40:31,070
I always hoped your
mother would look my way.

729
00:40:31,087 --> 00:40:35,581
One night, uh, she did,

730
00:40:35,596 --> 00:40:40,360
and after that,
we fell in love.

731
00:40:40,408 --> 00:40:42,343
Dad, if this is
too hard for you...

732
00:40:42,357 --> 00:40:45,253
No, no, I...

733
00:40:45,707 --> 00:40:48,830
I owe this to both of you.

734
00:40:48,847 --> 00:40:51,932
I could only sit back so long

735
00:40:51,947 --> 00:40:54,701
and let him treat
her the way he did.

736
00:40:54,718 --> 00:40:58,921
I remember hearing her screaming,
her crying,

737
00:40:58,936 --> 00:41:00,202
when he hit her,

738
00:41:00,218 --> 00:41:05,062
and finally one night,
I couldn't take it anymore.

739
00:41:09,168 --> 00:41:11,620
Next thing I know,

740
00:41:11,907 --> 00:41:13,833
he'd pulled a knife.

741
00:41:13,845 --> 00:41:15,963
So I...

742
00:41:17,048 --> 00:41:19,081
I hit him.

743
00:41:19,347 --> 00:41:24,432
Just kept hitting him.

744
00:41:27,936 --> 00:41:30,563
After that, we ran...

745
00:41:31,126 --> 00:41:33,692
and I never looked back,

746
00:41:34,675 --> 00:41:39,952
because I vowed I'd never take
my eyes off your mother again.

747
00:41:42,278 --> 00:41:47,420
I never applied for a green
card or amnesty because

748
00:41:47,657 --> 00:41:52,180
I was afraid they'd
send me back.

749
00:41:57,537 --> 00:42:02,230
I killed Ramiro Vasquez.

750
00:42:04,685 --> 00:42:08,373
Transcript : Raceman
